{
  "texts": [
    "Overall, the application, performance specifications and the volume of shipments (affecting the cost) will decide whether a more expensive monolithic EPIC with simpler packaging, a multi-chip 2.5D integration with more complex packaging, or a 3D integration with more complex processing/packaging is the right choice (Table 4).",
    "We expect that all of these scenarios will co-exist, just like in the electronics ecosystem.",
    "In this section, we describe the top technical impediments to the success of various silicon photonics applications (Table 5), connecting them to some of the challenges and opportunities discussed in previous sections.",
    "We limit the impediments to PIC/EIC technology only, excluding economic, regulatory, market, and other factors such as chemistry, biomarkers, quantum advantage, etc.",
    "We also do not delve into the benefits of silicon photonics for these applications since most of the previous works describe them in detail."
  ]
}